\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9
\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
In this video I want to explain why I removed the Marauder and replaced it with the Firebat. <break time="0.7s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
In the RTS genre, there is probably no more fundamental and iconic difference than that between melee and ranged units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
This difference is mechanically fascinating because melee units force you to fight for positioning, to get close enough to deal damage, and to recognize when it's time to retreat. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Typically, melee units are either very tanky, allowing them to withstand ranged fire long enough to get a few hits in (like the Zealot), or they are numerous and very fast (like Zerglings). <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
What they all have in common is that, once they are in range, they deal serious damage. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
This naturally creates more interaction between players and makes it crucial for both sides to choose the right moments to engage or disengage. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Up until now, especially in the bio playstyle, such a unit was missing. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Blizzard tried to fill this gap with the Hellbat, which is even classified as a biological unit, despite being built from a Factory and looking anything but "bio." <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The intention is clear \u8212\'97 it's supposed to be a human in a combat suit. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
But it never quite felt right, more like a forced solution to avoid having two very similar units, one from the Barracks and one from the Factory. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
It's also odd that you need to build Factories when you're trying to play bio, and stranger still that the Hellbat can be healed by Medivacs (the whole reason for its biological tag) but still cannot be loaded into a Bunker. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
It just doesn't fit together in a satisfying way. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Another reason the Firebat never made it into the Barracks lineup is that it looked too similar to the Marauder. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Blizzard's mission for StarCraft II was clear \u8212\'97 the very first T1 unit should stay recognizable from Brood War, but the first T1.5 unit for each race should be brand new. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
That's why we got Marauders instead of Firebats, Stalkers instead of Dragoons, and Roaches instead of early Hydralisks. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
This makes sense for a sequel \u8212\'97 you want players to instantly feel that this is a new game with fresh units. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
But when this design choice makes the gameplay worse, maybe it wasn't the right call after all, even if it made marketing StarCraft II easier. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The game already has plenty of unique qualities that set it apart from Brood War. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The Stalker, for example, is a great new addition, a natural evolution of the Dragoon, but the Marauder feels much less inspired. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
And the Roach? It's a fantastic design, but one that could have worked even better later in the tech tree, where its tankiness and "hit-and-run" style would be more impactful. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The Marauder, in contrast, is just a kind of "anti-armor Marine" that can't even shoot air. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The Stalker has Blink, an incredible tool for micro, and the Roach has Burrow Movement and hit-and-run potential. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
To make the Marauder more interesting, Blizzard gave it Concussive Shells so it could slow targets, but is getting slowed really an engaging mechanic? <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
In most cases, slows reduce micro potential rather than enhance it, and they often end up feeling frustrating or overpowered. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
They don't encourage interaction \u8212\'97 they limit it. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9
