\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Today I'm going to present the changes made to the Ghost. <break time="0.7s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The Ghost has a very powerful ability against Protoss with EMP, which is extremely hard to react to. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Additionally, with Snipe, the Ghost currently has a very strong tool against Zerg, which is also difficult to react to. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
On top of that, the Nuke ability is rarely used, and bio armies generally don't have much to counter flying massive units, since the Marine is the only Barracks unit besides the Ghost that can attack air. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Considering the Marine's relatively short range compared to Brood Lord, Tempest, and Colossus, it's often hard to deal with such units effectively. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Additionally, the Ghost is almost exclusively used for its abilities, while its basic attack, even in combination with Cloak, is rarely utilized on its own. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
In addition, with a lower skill level, it's also harder to use Snipe effectively compared to auto attacks, which just happen automatically. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
That's why I decided to make the Ghost's standard weapon more effective in general and especially against massive units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
It now deals bonus damage to massive and biological units instead to light units, and its range has been increased to 9. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Combined with its Cloak ability, the Ghost should now function well against more units and especially against massive and biological units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
From an immersion standpoint, this also fits nicely \u8212\'97 the Ghost is a sniper, and the increased range reflects that more clearly in gameplay. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
And the bonus damage against massive units can be explained by the idea that the Ghost is able to precisely target the vulnerable spots of large units. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
As part of this change, I've removed the Snipe ability. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
It was too focused on countering Zerg and was very difficult to react to. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Now, Ghosts have to attack an unit over a longer period of time to achieve the same amount of damage, Snipe would have done instantly. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
To make EMP more interesting and easier to react to, the Ghost now channels for 2 seconds before firing EMP at the target location. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
This gives opponents a window to recognize the cast and move their units out of the affected area. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
In addition, EMP disables detection from units for 15 seconds. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The affected units are Medics with Med Scanner active, Ravens, Overseers, Changelings, and Observers. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
(Yes, Medics have a detection ability, and Changelings can also detect burrowed and cloaked units within a short range.) <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
EMP no longer drains energy from burrowed units, but it instantly removes Defensive Matrix. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
EMP also reduces shields proportionally to increased HP and shield values. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Lastly, to make Nukes a more viable option, their build time has been significantly reduced, the impact delay slightly shortened, and their overall damage has been increased. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Now, with all these changes, Ghosts have the tools to be effective in more situations, while opponents have more opportunities to avoid taking heavy damage.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9
