\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
In this video, I present the changes to the Hellion. <break time="0.7s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The Hellion has an attack that hits multiple units in a line extending from the Hellion. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
This mechanic is very cool because it allows the unit's efficiency to increase if you move in very close, ideally into melee range, to enemy troops in order to hit as many units as possible. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
However, this mechanic works much worse when the unit has low HP. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The result is that the unit often only gets to fire once or twice, if at all, before dying. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
If you only fight with the unit from maximum range, you can minimize incoming damage, but its weapon then behaves like a normal single-target weapon (similar to a Marine or Hydralisk), which means the positive effect of this mechanic rarely comes into play, except perhaps against workers. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
And the lower the skill level, the harder it is to make use of, since it requires at least a certain amount of micro skill to get value out of the Hellion. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
With the Firebat, for example, it's better designed \u8212\'97 the Firebat has a lot of HP, even though its range is much shorter. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Since the Hellion's mechanic works best when it behaves like a melee unit, the Hellion would either need as much HP as a melee unit, or (like Zerglings) be mass-producible and cost-efficient enough that losing 10 of them wouldn't matter. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Neither solution really fits the Terran or the Hellion, for gameplay and visual reasons. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Therefore, I have given the Hellion a new weapon that throws incendiary grenades, which set an area on fire for a few seconds and deal damage over time and only little damage against the Hellion and Firebat. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
This allows the Hellion to zone a little, force the opponent to micro, harass worker lines more effectively, and deal damage without constantly being in the enemy's attack range. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
It also makes the Hellion more useful in the mid and late game and enables new unit combinations. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s19\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\sl276\slmult1\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\sb0\sa140\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\sl276\slmult1\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Its old weapon, as mentioned, fits much better on units with more HP, where this mechanic can be utilized more easily, making even beginners effective with this unit and only becoming more effective at higher skill levels \u8212\'97 especially when this unit can be healed and packed into bunkers. <break time="0.4s" /> Additionally, the Hellion takes less damage from Firebats to emphasize that both the Firebat and the Hellion have special armor against fire, making them work very well in combination. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The new weapon is less effective the better the opponent micros, but that's intentional, and it automatically makes the Hellion better against less mobile units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
And the transformation into the Hellbat no longer exists, since that role is now taken over by the Firebat.}
