\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
In today's video, I present the changes to the Siege Tank. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
The Siege Tank is the core of mech play, which is characterized by slowly pushing forward and forcing the opponent to act and break the siege. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
This threat has become less significant in StarCraft 2 due to the introduction of many new units and abilities that are well-suited to breaking such a siege. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Examples include Blink Stalkers, Immortals, Disruptors, Tempests, Burrowed Roaches, Swarm Hosts, Vipers, etc. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Overall, the Siege Tank has become easier to counter, but at the same time its improved movement AI, faster transformation time, and quicker firing rate give the opponent less time to react to a siege before game-ending damage can be dealt. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Additionally, we rarely see Siege Tanks fight in their mobile mode because they cannot withstand enough punishment there to deal efficient damage over their lifespan in battle, especially when compared to their resource and supply cost. <break time="1.2s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
Therefore, I have given Siege Tanks more HP, a little more range, and more damage. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
In return, the radius around the Siege Tank in which it cannot attack has been slightly increased, its attack speed slowed down, and its transformation time made longer. <break time="0.9s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
This gives players better opportunities to respond to sieges, while at the same time making sieges stronger once they are established. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af10\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\loch\cs17\rtlch\af11 \ltrch\hich\af4\loch\f4\dbch\af7\dbch\af9\loch
As a result, Terran mech play becomes somewhat slower, as intended, and opponents have a bit more time and space between tank volleys to use micro to gain an advantage.}
